                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480515-name-1451" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1451" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1451" type="surname" value="WONFER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1451" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH WONFER.</persName>
                  </hi> I live at No. 5, Caledonian-cottages, Battersea. I have one partner, named Edward Hoile—the prisoner was in my service—we were making alterations—we had a quantity of lead on our premises and factory.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ROBINSON.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you miss any? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—it was impossible—the prisoner was brought back and searched in my presence—this lead was found inside his trowsers—he said, "Pray forgive me"—he has been several years in service in that house—he was there when we took the premise—I believe this to be our property.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480515-name-1452" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1452" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1452" type="surname" value="HARDEMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1452" type="given" value="ALFRED"></interp>ALFRED HARDEMAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, V</hi> 73.) I took the prisoner. I found this piece of solder in his side pocket, and these forty-nine pounds of lead buttoned in the flap of his trowsers—this cord went round his neck to hold it up.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
